WRITING.TITLE: Is it even worth using select elements anymore when text inputs with autocomplete libraries provide so much more functionality?
WRITING.TEXT:
It seems that it has become standard practice to create "dropdowns" in UI with `input type="text"` and an accompanying JS plugin and datasource instead of plain `select`. The main reason being to overcome the issue of `selects` not having a string matching capability.
If you where creating a web application from ground up in 2016, would you ever consider using `select` over text input with some kind of autocomplete library?
